  <compounddef id="port__posix__socket_8c" kind="file" language="C++">
    <compoundname>port_posix_socket.c</compoundname>
    <briefdescription>
<para>POSIX socket implementation of the SyntropicOS socket port layer. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Provides UDP and TCP socket functions using the standard BSD/POSIX socket API. Works on any platform with POSIX sockets: Linux, macOS, ESP-IDF (lwIP), Zephyr, and any RTOS with a lwIP or POSIX socket shim.</para>
<para>Compile this file into your project alongside your platform&apos;s system port (e.g. <ref refid="port__esp32_8c" kindref="compound">port_esp32.c</ref> for GPIO/timer/UART) to get full networking support. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
